<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-03T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="344" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d344">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 811.001/360: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                                <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-03T17:00:00-04:00">October 3, 1919—5
                            p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 4—9 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                    <p>3327. Very [confidential for?] Polk. The President is very seriously ill and
                        unable to attend to any business. You should not therefore for the present
                        forward to him personal communications since they cannot be answered.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>